The South African navy is hosting the first-ever multinational maritime exercise. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African Navy is hosting its first-ever multinational maritime exercise in Cape Town. The five-day event with China and Russia officially starts on Monday. READ: 'No need to panic': authorities on Algoa Bay oil spill Ships from the two countries arrived at the Cape Town Harbour on Sunday. The theme of the exercise is Safe Navigation and Maritime Economic Security. There will also be training to see how a multinational task force will react to and counter security threats at sea.